Subject: [PATCH] Drop vendored-dep cmake.define defaults from pyproject.toml

The [tool.scikit-build.cmake.define] block hardcodes paths to
dependencies/lib/*.a static libs that only exist when upstream's
dependencies/scripts/download_dependencies.sh has been run to fetch
the UnoUtils.tar.gz binary bundle. For any other build (conda-forge,
distro packagers, system-libs source builds), those defaults break
the build because the paths don't exist.

Drop them; the same paths can be passed via cmake.args/cmake.define
by the consumer when needed.

--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -32,20 +32,3 @@
 cmake.verbose = true
 wheel.cmake = true
 wheel.packages = ["interfaces/Python/unopy"]  # point to a dir containing __init__.py
-
-# support for passing paths to dependencies from environment to CMake
-[tool.scikit-build.cmake.define]
-BLAS_LIBRARIES = "dependencies/lib/libblas.a;dependencies/lib/libcblas.a"
-LAPACK_LIBRARIES = "dependencies/lib/liblapack.a"
-# BQPD (cmake -DBQPD=/path/.../libbqpd.a)
-BQPD = "dependencies/lib/libbqpd.a"
-# MUMPS
-MUMPS_INCLUDE_DIR = "dependencies/include"
-METIS_INCLUDE_DIR = "dependencies/include"
-METIS_LIBRARY = "dependencies/lib/libmetis.a"
-MUMPS_LIBRARY = "dependencies/lib/libdmumps.a"
-MUMPS_COMMON_LIBRARY = "dependencies/lib/libmumps_common.a"
-MUMPS_PORD_LIBRARY = "dependencies/lib/libpord.a"
-MUMPS_MPISEQ_LIBRARY = "dependencies/lib/libmpiseq.a"
-# HiGHS
-HIGHS = "dependencies/lib/libhighs.a"
